the rest were undecided 
younger more educated and wealthier people were more apt to 
support legal abortion as were residents of the northeast and the 
west and bigcity dwellers people who called themselves 
conservatives were far more likely to oppose abortion just 42 
percent of conservatives supported the 1973 ruling compared with 
66 percent of moderates and 80 percent of liberals 
