<TEXT>
when sousuke uno became prime minister on june 2 
he was widely expected to be a caretaker who with luck might serve 
until october while his scandalplagued party put together a 
political reform package 
his luck turned out to be very bad 
now he will go down in japanese postwar history as rivaling for 
shortness the twomonth tenure that prime minister tanzan ishibashi 
had from december 1956 to february 1957 
seldom has a respectable political career crumbled as fast as 
unos he was in office less than a week when a weekly newsmagazine 
published a former geishas allegation that he had paid her to be 
his mistress 
publishing the story broke a taboo about revealing details of 
politicians private affairs the 66yearold uno who is married 
was deeply embarrassed facing opposition questions in parliament as 
