irans supreme religious leader following khomeinis death 
a national referendum that will be held alongside the 
presidential vote is expected to win approval for proposed 
constitutional amendments that will increase the presidents 
powers making him head of government and scrapping the post of 
prime minister 
the reforms will streamline irans government by eliminating 
competing power centers that have virtually paralyzed 
decisionmaking and delayed the formulation of a sound economic 
strategy following the ceasefire last august in the 8year war 
with iraq 
analysts say that election of the popular rafsanjani would usher 
