the tournament has been staged since 1977 on the grounds of the 
hulking brick castle that rises from a bluff overlooking the 
apartment blocks of the central poland town of golubdobrzyn 
at their aid are damsels recruited from a local high school 
competitors with crossbows hatchets and pronged mallets and 
thousands of common spectators whose murmers of respect and rumor 
someone almost had his nose sliced off spread the spirit of 
the event 
when i see the knights i think about reviving old traditions 
of knighthood said kwiatkowski 
it is not only the clothes but also reviving the spirit the 
old traditions honesty keeping promises honor these are 
features that today have lost their value but without which it is 
hard to live he said 
though bogged down by the demands of a modern knightmanager 
the castle director says he could still get on a horse and defend 
the honor of the polish knight 
those responsibilities fall mainly to the likes of remigiusz 
postolski a 30yearold warsaw art restorer who with his teammates 
bested the knights from italy france and the soviet union 
knight paulo parici of arezzo italy was awarded the golden 
sword for individual performance at the close of hostilities sunday 
almost every boy in poland when he is small reads books and 
watches films about knights and their fights for me it passed into 
a more serious interest postolski said 
most of the weapons armor and costumes are made by hand and 
modern knights must make some accommodations suits of armor ended 
with reebok sneakers and one crossbow champion wore skintight 
leggings of hot pink and black spandex below his coat of mail 
theres also the problem of how to sit on a slatted bench with a 
dagger at ones side 
the castle too has met the modern age the knights pledge of 
princely competition is made by microphone and a tv antenna rises 
from the ramparts flags and tablets mark great dates in castle 
history 1296 1527 1965 
the castle is owned by a government tourist agency much 
reconstructed from the ravages wrought by time and neglect it is 
still in need of defense fortifications against tourists without 
tickets 
but the hobbyists are loyal to the legends starting in 1385 when 
poland united with lithuania under the jagiellonian kings ruled a 
vast swath of central europe from the baltic to the black sea and 
stretching east toward moscow 
it was a time of cultural and scientific advancement when 
nicolas copernicus discovered the earths rotation around the sun 
and the jagiellonian university was established in krakow 
but from a polish knights point of view the eras highlight 
was likely the victory over the infamous teutonic knights a 
germanic order first established in 1191 for the crusades 
the most famous confrontation the battle of grunwald on july 
15 1410 took place about 50 miles from the castle and the victory 
of the polish and lithuanian forces over the teutonic camp after 
a knightly prebattle exchange of swords has lived on into the 
modern history of three nations 
kwiatkowski is an animated and unabashed fan of the 15th century 
what about poverty its exaggerated we have much bigger 
extremes in wealth today 
what about pestilence what about aids he retorts 
we poles have a kind of attraction to tradition and history 
added postolski whose sword bore the nicks of a few friendly 
rounds at that time our country was a european superpower 
</TEXT>
