a private memorial service will be held for 
donald barthelme an awardwinning modern fiction writer who died 
of cancer at the age of 58 
barthelme was known best for his wry humor and innovative 
techniques in short stories many of which were published in the 
new yorker atlantic and the paris review 
barthelme underwent successful surgery for throat cancer 17 
months ago but he became ill with a form of blood cancer while 
