<TEXT>
a slight tremor shook the us 
virgin islands monday and was felt in neighboring puerto rico the 
geophysical institute said no damage or casualties were reported 
the quake had a 49 magnitude on the richter scale and was 
centered 25 miles northwest of the island of st thomas said 
william mccan of the institute 
mccan said the institute received calls from puerto rico 
residents saying they also felt the tremor 
the richter scale is a measure of ground motion as recorded on 
seismographs every increase of one number means a tenfold increase 
in magnitude 
an earthquake of 4 on the richter scale can cause moderate 
damage in the local area and an earthquake measuring 5 on the scale 
can cause considerable damage 
