in a speech to the opening session of the threeday summit 
mubarak also urged the 50nation group to work together to confront 
racist aggression by south africa and ease africas debt 
problem 
mubarak called for the enhancement of solidarity for the 
settlement of the current disputes between various states 
he mentioned no specific conflicts but he clearly was referring 
to the border dispute between chad and libya the war between 
morocco and the polisario front over control of the western sahara 
