of the ultraorthodox agudat israel party to meet monday night and 
discuss whether to to withdraw support from prime minister yitzhak 
shamirs coalition government we have a secular court 
interfering in a religious subject said agudat legislator 
menachem porush the party has five seats of the 120 seats in 
parliament 
orthodox rabbis echoed religious affairs minister zevulun 
hammers pledge to renew the campaign for a narrower definition of 
who is a jew israel radio reported 
the problem remains as an open wound and will not be solved 
until it is solved at its roots that a jew is a jew only according 
to halacha chief rabbi avraham shapira of israels european 
jewish community said on israel radio halacha is orthodox jewish 
law 
