the united states cautioned the soviet union 
against trying to smuggle felix s bloch out of the country weeks 
before reports surfaced that the veteran american diplomat was 
suspected of being a spy it was learned monday 
president bush described reports of spying by bloch as very 
serious but did not offer an assessment of potential damage 
