forest fires raging through northern 
manitoba have forced the evacuation of more than 18000 people and 
smoke and flames threatened to block some escape routes 
the airport in thompson was reopened monday after radar 
equipment was flown in to help guide airplanes pilots were unable 
to locate the runways because of the dense smoke 
