tested a cable car he had designed for the city of san francisco 
the car pulled along by an underground cable traveled down clay 
street between jones and kearny first in a private test then in a 
public demonstration 
on this date 
in 1774 british scientist joseph priestley succeeded in 
isolating oxygen from air 
in 1790 the first us census was completed showing a 
population of nearly 4 million people in 13 states 
in 1834 an emancipation bill outlawed slavery throughout the 
british empire 
in 1876 colorado was admitted to the union as the 38th state 
in 1907 the forerunner of the us air force was established by 
the army as an aeronautical division 
