bobby vinton still singing about love 
and loneliness 27 years after his first hit record believes the 
title of his current album reflects his music timeless 
vinton a trim and youthful looking 54 continues to turn out 
romantic ballads reminiscent of roses are red his 1962 
breakthrough song on the national record charts 
the first single release from timeless is please tell her 
that i said hello which is about a man crying over an old lover 
other selections on the album include such love songs as getting 
used to being loved again and i made love with you tonight 
i feel my music is timeless vinton nicknamed the polish 
prince said in an interview roses are red and blue velvet 
still sound good today and you can relate to them there will 
always be that type of music there will always be a love singer a 
singer of stories and simplicity 
