products in february outbid dana corp which offered 590 million 
in cash and securities to acquire the spark plug maker 
dana a toledobased automotive parts manufacturer had signed 
an agreement to acquire champion in january champion had agreed to 
pay dana 15 million if the buyout fell through 
in making the bid for champion robert cizik coopers chairman 
and president said he had no objection to champions agreement to 
pay dana 
champion with annual revenue of about 730 million is the 
worlds leading manufacturer of spark plugs for all types of 
internal combustion engines it also manufactures anco windshield 
wiper blades and a variety of other fuel system and automotive 
maintenance products 
houstonbased cooper with annual revenue of 43 billion is a 
diversified worldwide manufacturer of products for the electrical 
electronic commercial industrial compression and drilling 
markets 
