bjorn borg said monday he refused an 
offer of fresh capital to rescue his struggling fashion business 
built on earnings from his 10year championship tennis career 
borg 33 said he turned down 46 million to help bjorn borg 
design group because he was afraid of losing control of his 
companies borg said he was negotiating other financing to keep his 
business afloat 
i remain committed to the business and am in the process of 
trying to reorganize the management and corporate structure of the 
group borg said in a statement 
bjorn borg design group produces a line of designer fashions 
fragrances shoes and accessories and has real estate interests in 
sweden 
lars skarke who has a 25 percent stake in borgs companies 
said the group was facing a a shortage of liquidity which is 
forcing the closure of the group 
the company needs an infusion of cash to meet orders and finance 
further expansion skarke was quoted as saying in the aftonbladet 
daily 
borg the fivetime wimbeldon champion who retired from 
professional tennis in 1983 has boasted of his handson management 
style making major business decisions on his own 
borg turned down an offer of 30 million kronor or 46 million 
by the mercuriusgroup ab to buy into the holding company bjorn 
borg enterprises ltd headquartered in monte carlo 
borg said the terms of the offer were not suitable to me as 
principal shareholder as proposed to me it would have meant 
surrendering financial control of the group 
he said he was not satisfied that we had ironed out the 
financial problems and indicated there were other offers that 
also were unacceptable borg said the cost structure was too high 
for the income notably in monte carlo and i have taken the 
appropriate action to remedy this 
borg who was pursued over the weekend amid reports the company 
was going bankrupt and being liquidated promised a fuller public 
report on the groups future once negotiations have been 
concluded 
borg who won wimbledon from 197680 and also took six french 
open titles was estimated to have earned 75 million in prizes and 
endorsements when he retired on his 1986 tax return borg placed 
his personal wealth at nearly 8 million 
borgs financial woes compounded other personal problems 
including a custody battle with his exgirlfriend jannike bjorling 
over his 3yearold son robin and plans to marry italian rock 
singer loredana berte which have been frustrated by delays in 
obtaining her divorce 
in february borg was treated in a milan italy hospital after 
taking sleeping pills but he dismissed speculation of a suicide 
attempt 
