on third world debt said that the mexican agreement appeared 
seriously flawed because it did not provide enough incentives for 
banks to opt for the two debtreduction options rather than simply 
piling on new debt 
a lot of the banks without the necessary carrots or sticks 
are going to stick with the familiar approach of supplying new 
money to pay old debt schumer said 
schumer said that approach has proven to be a disaster over the 
last seven years since 1982 when the debt crisis first erupted 
third world debt has more than doubled from 600 billion to 13 
trillion 
